      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GLOBAL FLASH (1) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fifth (22.80) last time in a Grade 5/6 at this track. Comes out of a solid form race last start. Can discover winning form. COLOUR OF RED (2) was safely held last time out, finishing fifth at this track over 400m behind All In Knots (23.50) in a Grade 5/6. Placed at his previous run. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to his credit. Cannot be taken lightly. ASTON CREMA (3) raced close to the lead throughout but collided with another runner, finishing a 2.5 lengths fourth (23.19) in a Grade 6 at this track. Better than last start and can bounce back. PINGELLY PRINCE (8) missed the placings here last start but is well-placed to make amends.",
